Selby, the 2014 winner from Leicester, led throughout Sunday and went into Monday's final session leading 14-11.
Ding, who was bidding to become the first Asian player to win the world title, claimed three frames in a row.
But Selby dug deep to seal a brilliant double for the city of Leicester, whose football team became Premier League champions 13 minutes earlier.
